Real recognises real! DJ Black Coffee,Mzansi's hottest musical export, shares the surreal moment when superstar rapper Drake held his hand and called him a Legend. In a video he shared on Twitter, Black Coffee recalled the moment he met Drake for the first time. "When I met Drake, he came over, he took my hand and held it down and he said 'legend'. That’s how it happened", Black Coffee said. Coffee said  he thought he would lose his mind meeting Drake. But when it happened, it the was Drake who was a fan of his. Drake and Black Coffee worked together on the remake of hit song Superman which they then called Get It Together released on Drake's 2017 album More LIfe. 